-- Equitable Life Names BlackRock to Manage $8.7 Billion Policyholder Funds
-- Mike Harrison
-- 2010-07-04T09:52:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-04/equitable-life-names-blackrock-to-manage-8-7-billion-policyholder-funds.html

          
          
             Equitable Life Assurance Society said
it has appointed BlackRock Inc. to provide investment and risk
management services for its 400,000 policyholders and group
scheme members.  
 “BlackRock’s objective will be to maximise returns on 5.7
billion pounds ($8.66 billion) of assets while satisfying
Equitable Life’s regulatory solvency ratios,” Equitable Life
said in an e-mailed statement today. The appointment will become
effective in October, it said.  
          
          


  


        